# Auth Patterns

## Getting the current user
Always use `getSession()` from `@/app/actions/auth` — never call Supabase auth directly in components:

```ts
// In server components / server actions
import { getSession } from '@/app/actions/auth'

const session = await getSession()
if (!session) redirect('/sign-in')
const { user } = session
```

## Supabase client in server context
```ts
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

// This reads the session cookie automatically
const supabase = await createClient()
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
```

## Avatar URLs
Always use `normalizeAvatarUrl()` — never access `user_metadata.avatar_url` directly.
Google OAuth stores the avatar in different fields depending on the sign-in method.
The normalize helper handles all cases.

## Protected routes
Gate server components at the top — do not render then redirect:

```tsx
// CORRECT — redirect before rendering
export default async function AccountPage() {
  const session = await getSession()
  if (!session) redirect('/sign-in')
  return <AccountUI user={session.user} />
}

// WRONG — renders then redirects (flashes content)
export default async function AccountPage() {
  const session = await getSession()
  return session ? <AccountUI /> : redirect('/sign-in')
}
```

## Admin-only routes
Check for admin role before any admin action or page render:

```ts
import { getSession } from '@/app/actions/auth'
import { getUserRole } from '@/app/actions/admin-roles'

const session = await getSession()
if (!session) redirect('/sign-in')
const role = await getUserRole(session.user.id)
if (role !== 'admin' && role !== 'superuser') redirect('/admin/access-denied')
```

## Auth redirect cookie
Use `AUTH_NEXT_COOKIE` (set in `app/actions/auth.ts`) to redirect users back after OAuth sign-in.
Do not invent a new cookie for this purpose.

## Do NOT
- Use `supabase.auth.getSession()` — use `supabase.auth.getUser()` (getSession can return stale data)
- Store user info in localStorage or client state — always re-fetch from the server on navigation
- Use the service role client to check auth — it bypasses RLS and will return the wrong data
